annotation.TEXT: Oh, nice. This ledge gets extended for weaker jumpers, which allows me to reach the power up block more easily.
Demo count: 10
I love the Blaster Master graphics used here.
Toasty!
Yep. I'm definitely going to mention this on the ER forums!
Totally blew my attempt at 5000 there...
There was a vote for any character whose name starts with "B", and they would be Bartz (Link), Benjamin (Link), Break Man (Mega Man), Bass, and Bill.
Hello, and welcome back to SMB Crossover! Up above are the voting results, yada, yada.
Am I stuck? Did ER fail to accommodate weaker jumpers here?
Just don't enter any of the pipes, since they'll all take you back to the beginning like I already showed, except in one case...
Huh. The brick pillar coming out of the ceiling here is one tile shorter than it should be, but maybe Crossover had issues with its original size, which would've required super plumbers to duck.
Looks like there's an extra platform here to help Bill out. (Why wasn't there an extra block or platform to help Bill out of that unwinnable situation earlier?)
Good thing for that double jump!
Huh, that was weird. I'll explain what I thought was weird in a moment.
Okay, I think I can ease up on the hurrying now. I'm getting close to the end, and still have plenty of time left.
COINS!!! I like how fast Bass can clean out coin blocks, but I hate how it takes Bass several shots to break regular bricks.
I think Bass's double jump should give him a decent chance at getting a perfect here.
Excellent!
Nuts! I didn't actually want to lift off into the stratosphere here! I want to stay down below in order to hit more blocks!
DOUBLE KILL!
Demo count: 12
Seeing how I'm getting ammo now, I guess I have every upgrade that Link can possibly get.
Alright, time for a random Luigi for the water level!
I'm not gonna waste nearly as much time this time around.
Now, this section repeats itself multiple times, and seems to look like a "maze" section. However, it's not actually a "maze", and it doesn't matter whether you choose the upper or lower routes here.
Nope, it's only an "M". Oh, well.
Huh, the shell went down that hole. Remember that for later.
Aw, an "F"? Well, it's better than nothing, I guess.
Alright, Bowser's fire, please don't screw me over here...
An "L"? Come on, I wanted the "S"!
Whoa, there Blooper. Get away from me.
I think it's Bill's turn next, and just like with Bass, I want to be sure I end up with a "B" character, so I'll just pick the Atari skin again.
That shell fell down the hole too. Now, there are three hidden coin blocks in obvious spots here, and there's a star in the center brick in the top row.
Oh, this is interesting. Looks like I just got my Magma Bazooka back, which is what Bass started with today.
There was also a vote for Dark Link, but that one didn't count, because it was made on episode [32 and a half], and as I've said before, I'm not counting votes made on "and a half" episodes.
There's another extra platform, and the bullets have stopped, so I guess I didn't really need to worry about them that much here.
Okay, what about Phoebe? Where's she located?
Now, Mega Man did get two votes, with one for Break Man, since he begins with "B", but I just used Proto Man not too long ago, so...
Of course, I will still stop for things like the hidden 1-up, this multi-coin block, and power ups.
In addition, both Luigi and Bill had one vote for B-2. However, since Bill had two other votes that didn't specify a level, I think I'll be using Luigi for B-2, and Bill elsewhere.
Shut up, clock.
Bowser's fire will start appearing when you're nearly done with this copy-and-paste environment, and if you enter the last pipe here...
Demo count: 13
Yeah, if I'm up against a wall while facing left, Luigi doesn't turn and face right when I press right, until I move away from the wall first.
Going up!
YAAAAHHH!!! It's just as well, since I only had 1 tick left on the clock anyway. I simply wasted too much time on stupid stuff following the sky bonus area.
But wait, Mario got no votes this time, and Benjamin (Link) got one vote, so why am I going with Mario now? Well, there is a reason.

I'll start with Bass, but I'm not gonna just go with a random skin, because I might end up with a character whose name doesn't start with "B". I'll go with the Atari Bass (who is still called "Bass" here).
Nope. Gotta die. Bye, Mario!
Yeah, it just depends on whether the double jump gives Bass enough height or not.
Meh. That fish can live.
Let's try this again...
I think I'll skip the sky bonus this time, since that consumed a lot of time last time. (Getting the perfect was still worth it to me, though.)
And that, shall we say, is that.
Ah, I see that there's an extra platform right at the start here to help Bill make the first jump.
Um, what is that item? I can't tell just by looking at its Atari graphics...
BURN! BURN TO THE GROUND! BURN! BURN TO THE GROUND! WOO! TRI-FORMATION! BURN TO THE GROUND! BURN! BURN!
...You end up somewhere entirely different!
Alright, I'm almost there. This time, let's not head down the pipe leading to the warp zone.
I'll once again grab the star, since it's totally a good thing to get, but I'm going to avoid the green springboard this time.
Hmm... In thinking about it, maybe I should've used Break Man for B-2 instead of Luigi. Then, I would've ended up using four different "B" characters today. Oh, well.
I'm trying to anticipate his jumps now.
Aw, no Blaster Master graphics this time. (But I'm not gonna bother going through the menus to put the Blaster Master graphics back.)
Can I use the pause trick to defeat this guy with one grenade like with some Blaster Master bosses? Nah, I highly doubt it.
To be continued... Yo!
D'oh! That wasn't in the script.
Oh, I'm way too low on time now! I don't think I'm gonna make it!
There's a vine there that I fully intend to climb up in a moment.
...I'm-a gonna go-a with-a Space-a Mario-a!
There we go. That's how the jump should've gone last time.
Ah, it's the Flame Blast from Mega Man 6. Why is it colored greenish now? Is it due to the Atari graphics, or because I'm using Bass?
Well, that sucked, having Luigi lose his fire power to something stupid like that... Otherwise, that level went alright.
Looks like the moving platform under this ? block has been lowered one space.
Still got 2000 plus six fireworks, though.
SMW Luigi it is!
...Wait a minute... I don't think Bill can make that next jump to the right, and the "M" block is too high to jump onto...
The music changed because I'm low on time. I'm not worried, though.
No, thanks. I don't want the "F". However, I would like to get one more "R" if at all possible. Last time I was offered an "R", it was on a block that was too high to jump onto in world 8-2.
D'oh! I could've sworn I hit the jump button again to double jump before getting bitten there. Of course, why'd I even go around the top there in the first place?
Okay, this hidden 1-up is in the right spot, which is exactly as I remembered, so my memory isn't totally wonky.
Oh, come on! That stupid fish in the wall there actually hit me?! That wouldn't happen in the same situation in the original games.
Now, it's Benjamin's turn to play this level for realsies.

Now, at least the whole level isn't unwinnable due to this level design flaw. As long as I don't drop all the way down to where those two lowest coins are, I should be fine, and I can still open the power up block from above.
And it does! (I think dash-jumping gives me a little more height with my first jump.)
Nice. I timed that right.
Yep, this is where the warp to world D is. However, I don't actually want to warp, but backtracking at this point is impossible, so I've gotta kill myself now, unless maybe this pipe is two-way...
Sky bonus perfects: 3
Unfortunately, while other characters can exit the water in places like this, Mario and Luigi have to adhere to the original SMB rules and can't jump out of the water.
I guess I'll sometimes let fish live if they're not in my way.
Now, this time, I did want to enter the stratosphere!
Yep, I was only about one screen away from the end when I bit it last time.

I thought I remembered there being a poison mushroom in one of those first seven ? blocks, but I checked B-1's map from the original Lost Levels afterwards, and it doesn't show a poison mushroom there, so I guess I remembered wrong.
Since it doesn't matter which routes I take during this part, I'm just gonna stick with the lower routes, since they're slightly easier (don't need to jump over the fire bars).
Alright, I don't think I missed too much back here. Just half a dozen ? blocks that all contain coins. Uh, oh... I'm low on time here.
...I get sent back here. In the original Lost Levels, this is useful for double-dipping on the power up block, but that doesn't work in Crossover.

Alright, world B is done, and I've now shown every warp zone in the game! (Surprisingly, there's no backwards warp to world A anywhere, I don't think...) So, who should I use for world C? Place your votes now!
Now, in this next section, if I enter the first pipe here...
Oh, and even though I was near the end, there are no checkpoints anywhere in worlds 8 and above, so I have to start over from the beginning. Just swell.
I like how I was allowed to duck-jump there even though I was small. (I instinctively did that so my head wouldn't be instantly overlapping the base of the fire bar after I grew.)
Demo count: 11
DOUBLE KILL!
Oh, well. At least I didn't have any power ups to lose. Now, let's try this again, shall we?
Alright, it's boss time! If I keep my distance and just keep throwing my sword beams, this should be no problem.
Uh, oh. Maybe I should've kept the "F" for these Bullet Bills.
Can I at least have my AWESOME SPREAD GUN back?
Also, Blaster Master graphics again FTW! Oh, and I like this Final Fantasy 1 music as well.
Huh, this time the shell didn't fall down either hole. I wonder if ER will ever fix the kicked shell physics in this game...
Pfft... Of course I go and miss an early coin just like that. However, since backtracking is possible, I could still actually get the perfect!
And that's why I initially chose Mario for this level, because he didn't have any power ups to lose right now, and I knew that I'd probably have to suicide after showing the world D warp zone.
Gotta stop to kill some enemies too, of course. I wouldn't want to be clobbered by them simply because I was way too hasty.
And yes, there's actually a super-duper-uber fire bar down here.
Actually, I want to land here to get the coins below, and one of those blocks has a power up as well. Maybe it'll be an "R"?
